00:19:10.070 --> 00:19:12.440
that we have to test over
and over and over again.

00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:14.520
So lots of questions--
absolutely no

00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:16.480
precedents for this.

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:18.050
We're trying our best guesses.

00:19:18.050 --> 00:19:19.040
This is our process.

00:19:19.040 --> 00:19:20.350
We try our best guesses.

00:19:20.350 --> 00:19:21.830
We prototype every day.

00:19:21.830 --> 00:19:23.760
We're prototyping
and prototyping.

00:19:23.760 --> 00:19:26.020
And we're refining
over and over again.

00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:29.100
Frankly, it's a
really long process

00:19:29.100 --> 00:19:30.360
with lots of uncertainty.

00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:32.880
And as we chip away at it,
we get closer and closer

00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:35.260
to something that we believe in.

00:19:35.260 --> 00:19:38.190
So the software engineers
and the digital designers

00:19:38.190 --> 00:19:41.610
on this project, as opposed
to the industrial designers,

00:19:41.610 --> 00:19:43.650
we have a unique challenge.

00:19:43.650 --> 00:19:46.360
So for one, the prototype
is almost entirely

00:19:46.360 --> 00:19:48.900
controlled through a phone app.

00:19:48.900 --> 00:19:51.730
It's literally the
keys to your car.

00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:53.720
So there are not a lot
of phone apps out there

00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:55.980
that have that level
of mission-critical

00:19:55.980 --> 00:19:57.360
responsibility.

00:19:57.360 --> 00:20:00.310
The only experience I can think
of that comes close to this

00:20:00.310 --> 00:20:02.380
is when you use an
electronic boarding pass

00:20:02.380 --> 00:20:04.560
when you go to the airport.

00:20:04.560 --> 00:20:06.870
If your phone dies, you're
not getting on that plane.

00:20:06.870 --> 00:20:09.170
But you do have another option.

00:20:09.170 --> 00:20:11.890
You can hassle the gate agent
to print you another one.

00:20:11.890 --> 00:20:12.834
You wait in that line.

00:20:12.834 --> 00:20:14.000
They're usually pretty busy.

00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:17.160
So it's kind of a hassle,
but it's not a huge deal.

00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:22.020
So it's not quite an
analogy, but it's close.

00:20:22.020 --> 00:20:25.080
We're also working
hard at creating trust.

00:20:25.080 --> 00:20:27.210
I think a lot of
new technologies

00:20:27.210 --> 00:20:29.040
have this challenge.

00:20:29.040 --> 00:20:31.610
But seeing that this
is a moving vehicle,

00:20:31.610 --> 00:20:33.810
it's even more important
to let the user know

00:20:33.810 --> 00:20:34.730
what the car knows.

